1
00:01:29,460 --> 00:01:34,940
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,220 --> 00:01:37,789
[Episode 12]

3
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:39,310
Mr. Ding.

4
00:01:39,330 --> 00:01:40,789
Xiaoman left you a letter.

5
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,130
Left me what?

6
00:01:47,509 --> 00:01:48,509
Left you a letter.

7
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:49,340
Where is he?

8
00:01:50,509 --> 00:01:51,590
He went to Shanghai.

9
00:01:51,590 --> 00:01:52,850
He left carrying a bag.

10
00:01:57,509 --> 00:01:58,640
Where is the letter?

11
00:01:58,870 --> 00:01:59,800
It's by the door.

12
00:02:17,910 --> 00:02:20,000
Uncle Ding, don't worry about me.

13
00:02:20,250 --> 00:02:22,030
I just don't want to sit around waiting

14
00:02:22,030 --> 00:02:23,760
for Xiaodan and Xia Lei to call.

15
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,250
I want to see them in person

16
00:02:25,250 --> 00:02:27,030
and have a proper talk with them.

17
00:02:27,030 --> 00:02:27,960
Besides,

18
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,190
I've hardly

19
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:31,820
ever left East Chemical Plant in my life.

20
00:02:31,870 --> 00:02:34,230
I've only ever seen Shanghai in pictures
on calendars.

21
00:02:34,230 --> 00:02:36,030
I should go out and see the world.

22
00:03:05,750 --> 00:03:06,310
Well, uh...

23
00:03:06,310 --> 00:03:06,910
Excuse me.

24
00:03:06,910 --> 00:03:09,800
Um, do you know
where the Architecture Department is?

25
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:12,260
The Architecture Department?
That's my department.

26
00:03:12,260 --> 00:03:13,060
You are?

27
00:03:13,450 --> 00:03:15,520
I-In that case, do you know Xiaodan?

28
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,250
Yan Xiaodan?

29
00:03:16,470 --> 00:03:18,079
What is her major,

30
00:03:18,079 --> 00:03:19,810
and what's her concentration?

31
00:03:19,910 --> 00:03:22,110
Architecture. Just... architecture.

32
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,170
You don't go to this school, do you?

33
00:03:25,870 --> 00:03:27,240
That building in the back,

34
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,079
Building No. 2,

35
00:03:28,079 --> 00:03:29,810
is our main academic building.

36
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,000
Thank you. Thank you.

37
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:31,630
No problem.

38
00:03:31,630 --> 00:03:33,079
No. 2... No. 2, right?

39
00:03:33,470 --> 00:03:34,360
The one in the back!

40
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,450
Nice.

41
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:36,560
If we keep building it
like Xiaodan is doing,

42
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:38,420
our group could take first place.

43
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:42,680
You've built it so high.

44
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,840
Should we add another piece? Well...

45
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:46,240
Let's try one more piece?

46
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:47,120
I don't really dare anymore.

47
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:50,380
-Look at this—maybe we shouldn't.
-The structure isn't very stable.

48
00:03:50,380 --> 00:03:52,240
How about pushing it to the limit?

49
00:03:52,870 --> 00:03:53,520
Let's add one more piece?

50
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:54,400
If it falls,

51
00:03:54,430 --> 00:03:55,870
it'll be hard to rebuild.

52
00:03:55,870 --> 00:03:56,590
It won't.

53
00:03:57,310 --> 00:03:58,770
Let me think. Let me think.

54
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,930
If I add another, I'll put it here...

55
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:07,470
Xiaodan.

56
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,410
Do you know that guy?

57
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:10,680
What guy?

58
00:04:10,870 --> 00:04:13,400
That one.
He's been staring at you for a while.

59
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:17,890
Xiaoman!

60
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:22,250
How did you get here?

61
00:04:24,270 --> 00:04:26,310
I got... I got the letter you wrote me.

62
00:04:26,310 --> 00:04:28,160
So... So I came.

63
00:04:28,270 --> 00:04:29,470
Have you lost weight?

64
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:31,560
No. But your thing fell over.

65
00:04:32,030 --> 00:04:32,710
It's okay.

66
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:37,909
My boyfriend.

67
00:04:40,990 --> 00:04:42,450
It's fine. Go back to class.

68
00:04:42,450 --> 00:04:44,060
You came all this way. I...

69
00:04:44,270 --> 00:04:44,830
It's okay.

70
00:04:44,830 --> 00:04:47,000
I'm happy just staying with you,
whatever we do.

71
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,030
Go ahead. I'll wait for you.

72
00:04:48,030 --> 00:04:49,490
-Okay. Wait for me.
-Okay.

73
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:50,940
I'll come to you after class.

74
00:04:50,940 --> 00:04:51,420
Okay.

75
00:04:52,870 --> 00:04:53,870
Sorry. Sorry.

76
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,050
I was so excited.

77
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:57,560
What should we do now?
We were just saying we wanted first place.

78
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:59,430
It's okay. We understand.

79
00:05:00,430 --> 00:05:02,960
Honestly, your boyfriend is
quite handsome.

80
00:05:03,790 --> 00:05:04,790
He's really nice.

81
00:05:05,470 --> 00:05:06,200
Good for you.

82
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:10,160
Xia Lei and I called Uncle Ding
a couple of days ago,

83
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:12,420
but we couldn't get through to him at all.

84
00:05:13,510 --> 00:05:13,920
Yeah.

85
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:17,120
Well... Uncle Ding's phone was broken,

86
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,780
so the call didn't go through.

87
00:05:19,510 --> 00:05:21,170
Does Xia Lei know you're here?

88
00:05:21,310 --> 00:05:22,060
No, he doesn't.

89
00:05:22,060 --> 00:05:22,680
I didn't have time to tell him.

90
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:23,940
I haven't told anyone.

91
00:05:24,570 --> 00:05:25,770
How about this?

92
00:05:26,180 --> 00:05:27,620
We'll go back to my dorm in a bit.

93
00:05:27,620 --> 00:05:28,680
I'll call Xia Lei,

94
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:29,970
say there's something urgent,

95
00:05:29,970 --> 00:05:30,870
and have him come over.

96
00:05:30,870 --> 00:05:32,110
Let's surprise him. What do you think?

97
00:05:32,110 --> 00:05:32,870
That sounds good.

98
00:05:32,870 --> 00:05:33,630
Let's scare him.

99
00:05:33,630 --> 00:05:35,680
-Yeah, yeah.
-Let's see how he reacts.

100
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:36,120
Right.

101
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:37,120
He won't see me

102
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:37,680
hiding here, right?

103
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:38,800
Right. Don't move.

104
00:05:38,870 --> 00:05:40,310
Don't move. Lower. Get lower.

105
00:05:40,310 --> 00:05:41,640
Why are you pressing me down?

106
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:42,870
Hurry. He's coming. He's coming.

107
00:05:42,870 --> 00:05:43,510
He can't see you.

108
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:44,440
He can't see you.

109
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:48,750
Is he here yet?

110
00:05:48,750 --> 00:05:49,310
Almost, almost.

111
00:05:49,310 --> 00:05:50,270
Don't move.

112
00:05:51,830 --> 00:05:53,120
It's just a few steps—he's still not here?

113
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:54,720
H-He's not very agile.

114
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,830
All he's good at is studying.

115
00:05:56,830 --> 00:05:57,690
Still not here?

116
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:59,270
Almost, almost. He's here!

117
00:05:59,870 --> 00:06:02,480
Xiaoman, happy birthday!

118
00:06:02,580 --> 00:06:04,190
Happy birthday, Xiaoman!

119
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:05,510
Happy birthday!

120
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:08,210
Didn't expect it, huh?

121
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:09,510
Surprised?

122
00:06:10,270 --> 00:06:11,360
Ready, go.

123
00:06:11,830 --> 00:06:15,510
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

124
00:06:15,830 --> 00:06:18,040
♪ Happy birthday to Zhang Xiaoman ♪

125
00:06:19,490 --> 00:06:20,870
Happy birthday, Xiaoman!

126
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:22,720
And congratulations on coming of age.

127
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:23,450
Right.
Congratulations on becoming an adult!

128
00:06:23,450 --> 00:06:24,560
You're an adult now.

129
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:26,180
We should've put that hat on him just now.

130
00:06:26,180 --> 00:06:27,240
It's not too late to put it on now.

131
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:27,890
Hurry up.

132
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,510
Let him wear it and make a wish.

133
00:06:29,510 --> 00:06:30,070
Come on.

134
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:32,430
No. I... I...

135
00:06:32,430 --> 00:06:33,270
Blessings in the candlelight.

136
00:06:33,270 --> 00:06:35,000
No. I'll wear it as a scarf instead.

137
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,860
-Around my neck.
-Let me help you.

138
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:38,620
Okay, it's on.

139
00:06:38,620 --> 00:06:39,600
Does it look better like this?

140
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:40,720
It does. Hurry, make a wish.

141
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:43,270
Okay. There are three candles here.

142
00:06:43,690 --> 00:06:45,690
Just like the three of us.

143
00:06:46,510 --> 00:06:47,570
Together forever,

144
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:49,170
never apart.

145
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:51,970
But you said your wish out loud—

146
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,980
does that mean it won't come true?

147
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:55,480
I think it really depends on what we do.

148
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:56,270
And the three of us

149
00:06:56,270 --> 00:06:58,870
have to work on
this particular wish together.

150
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:00,540
-Blow them.
-Blow.

151
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:05,830
-Happy birthday.
-Happy birthday.

152
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:07,170
Let me see what it says.

153
00:07:07,170 --> 00:07:09,480
May 21st—we all love you.

154
00:07:09,510 --> 00:07:10,640
Happy Coming-of-Age.

155
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:12,270
That's quite romantic of you.

156
00:07:12,270 --> 00:07:14,130
It comes straight from the heart.

157
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:16,720
You two are quite something.

158
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:18,560
Y-You tricked me.

159
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:21,310
She lied and said we should surprise you,

160
00:07:21,310 --> 00:07:23,000
but it turns out
you two teamed up to surprise me.

161
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:25,720
Well, your sudden arrival was
already a surprise in itself.

162
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:27,480
And when Xiaodan first told me,

163
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:28,800
I was so stunned

164
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,510
I thought I'd misheard.

165
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,630
So we threw this together in a rush.

166
00:07:32,630 --> 00:07:35,120
And this cake is just so-so.

167
00:07:35,510 --> 00:07:36,430
Isn't it nice?

168
00:07:36,570 --> 00:07:37,360
Three flowers—

169
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:39,890
like the three of us,
all blooming flowers.

170
00:07:41,140 --> 00:07:42,000
Blooming forever.

171
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,270
The age of blooming.

172
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,270
It's good! Very good!

173
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,510
Why are there no stars

174
00:07:51,510 --> 00:07:53,110
in the Shanghai sky at night?

175
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:57,360
Maybe it's because of
the architectural nightscape—

176
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:58,360
all the lighting.

177
00:07:58,510 --> 00:07:59,240
What's that?

178
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,070
I just learned it. Basically,

179
00:08:01,070 --> 00:08:03,510
decorative lighting on buildings

180
00:08:03,510 --> 00:08:05,830
does brighten the city at night,

181
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:08,100
but it also washes out the starlight.

182
00:08:08,110 --> 00:08:09,600
Gosh, that's a pity.

183
00:08:10,550 --> 00:08:11,610
Let's cut the cake.

184
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:13,560
Come on.

185
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:14,680
You do it.

186
00:08:14,740 --> 00:08:15,230
Come on.

187
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:16,670
Where should I cut?

188
00:08:16,670 --> 00:08:17,670
Cut here. Here.

189
00:08:22,140 --> 00:08:23,650
You know, Magellan

190
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:25,000
traveled to so many places.

191
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,430
But I bet he never went in circles

192
00:08:26,430 --> 00:08:28,510
around the same spot this many times.

193
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,560
Back in the old days,

194
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:32,870
you know what they'd call this?

195
00:08:32,870 --> 00:08:33,510
What?

196
00:08:33,870 --> 00:08:35,510
"A donkey pulling a millstone."

197
00:08:35,510 --> 00:08:37,480
-Going round and round in the same spot.
-You're so annoying.

198
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,360
What nonsense.

199
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:40,270
But look,

200
00:08:40,270 --> 00:08:43,270
this track doesn't have a finish line.

201
00:08:43,510 --> 00:08:45,120
And since there's no finish line,

202
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:45,840
we can

203
00:08:45,870 --> 00:08:47,600
just keep walking

204
00:08:47,620 --> 00:08:48,620
forever and ever.

205
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:52,840
But we can't just keep going
in circles forever, right?

206
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:53,240
It's okay.

207
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:55,240
I can accompany you wherever you go.

208
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:57,480
And if you ever pull ahead,

209
00:08:58,030 --> 00:09:00,270
I'll just run a few steps to catch up.

210
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:05,510
Then, as you're running to catch up,
you'll look up

211
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:07,310
and find me right in front of you.

212
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:10,760
Or you'll turn around and find me
still right behind you.

213
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:27,390
Your school's environment

214
00:09:27,390 --> 00:09:28,250
is really nice.

215
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,850
Where do you want to take me?

216
00:09:31,550 --> 00:09:33,010
Let's see if you can guess.

217
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:35,640
What does Shanghai have

218
00:09:35,670 --> 00:09:37,550
that the East Chemical Plant doesn't?

219
00:09:37,550 --> 00:09:38,480
There's plenty.

220
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:40,820
The Oriental Pearl Tower, right?

221
00:09:41,510 --> 00:09:43,320
The Bund.
Our plant doesn't have that either.

222
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,960
And that... that hotel.

223
00:09:44,980 --> 00:09:47,180
Our plant doesn't have that. None of it.

224
00:09:47,870 --> 00:09:48,670
Wrong.

225
00:09:49,070 --> 00:09:49,510
Then what is it?

226
00:09:49,510 --> 00:09:50,720
I'll give you a hint.

227
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:54,510
I must be a kapok tree,
standing beside you.

228
00:09:55,150 --> 00:09:57,600
As trees, we stand together.

229
00:09:57,670 --> 00:09:58,240
Right?

230
00:09:59,750 --> 00:10:00,480
What?

231
00:10:01,270 --> 00:10:02,270
Trees.

232
00:10:04,370 --> 00:10:05,600
I-I haven't seen them yet.

233
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:07,460
What do those two trees look like?

234
00:10:07,510 --> 00:10:10,840
So we'll go to a park later
to find an oak tree

235
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:12,630
and see if there really is a kapok tree

236
00:10:12,630 --> 00:10:14,920
standing right beside it.

237
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:15,870
Sure.

238
00:10:16,150 --> 00:10:16,840
It's a deal.

239
00:10:16,860 --> 00:10:17,390
Let's go.

240
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:18,270
It fell off.

241
00:10:24,060 --> 00:10:24,540
Dad.

242
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:28,360
-Chief Engineer Yan.
-Xiaoman.

243
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:29,480
You came all the way to Shanghai

244
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,340
and didn't come to say hello to me?

245
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:32,270
Well... um...

246
00:10:32,270 --> 00:10:32,720
Wait, Dad.

247
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:33,870
How did you know Xiaoman came to Shanghai?

248
00:10:33,870 --> 00:10:35,360
Your Uncle Ding told me.

249
00:10:35,510 --> 00:10:37,360
He said you left a note and ran off.

250
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:38,030
Right?

251
00:10:39,670 --> 00:10:40,150
Yes.

252
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:45,100
Don't you have classes today?

253
00:10:45,290 --> 00:10:48,490
I have a general class
in the third period this afternoon.

254
00:10:49,150 --> 00:10:50,630
Alright, it's noon.

255
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,150
Let's have lunch together.

256
00:10:52,150 --> 00:10:54,950
Let me check out the food
at your school cafeteria.

257
00:10:59,150 --> 00:10:59,870
You okay?

258
00:11:00,150 --> 00:11:00,680
I'm fine.

259
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:01,960
-It's nothing.
-Why did he suddenly

260
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:03,000
come to your school?

261
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,240
It's okay. Let's go.

262
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:06,630
My dad knows
we celebrated your birthday belatedly,

263
00:11:06,630 --> 00:11:08,380
so he specifically ordered
a bowl of birthday noodles for you.

264
00:11:08,380 --> 00:11:08,840
Really?

265
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:13,150
There's no cake,

266
00:11:13,150 --> 00:11:15,720
so just make do with
a bowl of longevity noodles, okay?

267
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:16,510
Thank you, Uncle Yan.

268
00:11:16,510 --> 00:11:17,150
See?

269
00:11:17,270 --> 00:11:18,150
You got what you wanted.

270
00:11:18,150 --> 00:11:18,790
There's seafood here.

271
00:11:18,790 --> 00:11:21,120
We asked them to
add it especially for you.

272
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:23,280
I wonder how it tastes.

273
00:11:23,420 --> 00:11:24,150
Let me try it.

274
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:27,790
How is it?

275
00:11:29,670 --> 00:11:30,600
I'm telling you,

276
00:11:31,150 --> 00:11:32,860
this is the best bowl of noodles
I've ever had.

277
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:33,700
Then eat more.

278
00:11:36,910 --> 00:11:37,510
Xiaoman.

279
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:40,720
My transfer order came so suddenly
this time

280
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:42,670
that I rushed to Shanghai.

281
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:44,960
Otherwise, by all rights,

282
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:47,030
I should've personally gone to
pick you up.

283
00:11:47,030 --> 00:11:48,120
No need. It's fine.

284
00:11:48,150 --> 00:11:50,440
Uh... Mr. Ding picked me up.

285
00:11:50,970 --> 00:11:51,670
It was nothing, actually.

286
00:11:51,670 --> 00:11:53,120
I went straight home.

287
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,150
Everything went smoothly.

288
00:11:54,150 --> 00:11:55,000
Speaking of which,

289
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,510
I really have to thank you.

290
00:11:57,240 --> 00:11:58,910
If you hadn't stood up for Xiaodan,

291
00:11:58,910 --> 00:12:01,770
she wouldn't have gotten into college
so smoothly.

292
00:12:02,750 --> 00:12:04,120
No. A-Actually,

293
00:12:04,150 --> 00:12:05,510
that had nothing to do with her
to begin with.

294
00:12:05,510 --> 00:12:06,840
I caused the trouble.

295
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:09,120
If anything, I dragged Xiaodan into it.

296
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:09,910
Whoever it was—

297
00:12:09,910 --> 00:12:11,120
you or Xiaodan—

298
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,510
as long as you're kids from our plant,

299
00:12:12,510 --> 00:12:14,320
it's my responsibility
to look out for you.

300
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:14,720
Yes.

301
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:16,120
Dad, we're eating.

302
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:17,120
Why bring this up?

303
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:18,920
Are you going to let us eat or not?

304
00:12:20,150 --> 00:12:21,270
I can't eat.

305
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:22,340
How about this?

306
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:24,360
Go buy some drinks for us.

307
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:25,240
I'll go. I'll go.

308
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:25,550
What do you want?

309
00:12:25,550 --> 00:12:26,510
No, you don't know the area.

310
00:12:26,510 --> 00:12:28,360
Let Xiaodan go. Go buy some drinks.

311
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:29,150
W-What do you want to drink?

312
00:12:29,150 --> 00:12:30,410
Whatever. You decide.

313
00:12:30,670 --> 00:12:32,720
Okay. The card's with me.

314
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:38,970
Xiaoman.

315
00:12:40,150 --> 00:12:43,150
You... didn't even say a word

316
00:12:43,150 --> 00:12:45,280
and just ran off to Shanghai like that.

317
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:46,960
Do you know how worried Uncle Ding was

318
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:48,000
when he called me?

319
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:50,150
I know.

320
00:12:50,150 --> 00:12:53,840
I really didn't think it through
this time.

321
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,720
I wanted to wait for Xiaodan's call
at home,

322
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:58,000
but it d-didn't come.

323
00:12:58,120 --> 00:13:00,750
I got anxious and just rushed over.

324
00:13:01,270 --> 00:13:02,510
I handled this poorly.

325
00:13:02,510 --> 00:13:04,110
I really have to lecture you.

326
00:13:04,510 --> 00:13:06,080
You're a grown-up now,

327
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:06,720
right?

328
00:13:07,270 --> 00:13:09,510
You can't just act on impulse anymore.

329
00:13:09,670 --> 00:13:12,400
You have to learn to
consider other people's feelings—

330
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:14,360
especially those who care about you,
love you,

331
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:15,490
and worry about you.

332
00:13:15,910 --> 00:13:16,970
Yes, I understand.

333
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,150
It's just this once.

334
00:13:18,150 --> 00:13:19,910
I promise I won't do it again.

335
00:13:19,910 --> 00:13:20,750
No next time, alright?

336
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:21,360
Yes.

337
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:22,720
Eat up.

338
00:13:26,510 --> 00:13:27,570
You know, Xiaoman,

339
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:29,510
I went to great lengths to

340
00:13:29,510 --> 00:13:32,750
get transferred back to Shanghai
this time.

341
00:13:33,150 --> 00:13:34,480
It was all for Xiaodan.

342
00:13:35,790 --> 00:13:37,120
I can't guarantee

343
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:39,150
I can pave the way for her whole life,

344
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:42,090
but at least I have to
get her out of the mountains.

345
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:47,020
Xiaodan has always been a good student.

346
00:13:47,070 --> 00:13:48,370
She's good at everything.

347
00:13:48,370 --> 00:13:51,080
I believe she'll succeed in the future.

348
00:13:51,150 --> 00:13:52,880
She'll realize all her dreams.

349
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:56,440
I hope she'll have a future
full of possibilities.

350
00:13:58,150 --> 00:14:00,720
I can't let her future be bound to
the East Chemical Plant.

351
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:01,650
Don't you agree?

352
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:14,850
Chief Engineer Yan.

353
00:14:15,790 --> 00:14:17,000
I... I came this time

354
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:20,390
and saw Xiaodan studying here.

355
00:14:20,390 --> 00:14:21,510
The school's good.

356
00:14:21,630 --> 00:14:22,510
Everything is great.

357
00:14:22,510 --> 00:14:25,510
Honestly, I feel... reassured.

358
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:30,120
I won't stay long.

359
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:31,380
I'll go back tomorrow.

360
00:14:32,630 --> 00:14:35,080
That's not what I meant.
Stay as long as you like.

361
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:37,110
It's fine. Since I left home

362
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,670
and came straight to Shanghai,

363
00:14:38,670 --> 00:14:39,990
I should visit family while I'm here.

364
00:14:39,990 --> 00:14:40,870
Right, right.

365
00:14:41,540 --> 00:14:43,670
Give them my regards when you see them.

366
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:44,380
No problem.

367
00:14:44,890 --> 00:14:49,080
Also... whatever comes up
back at the plant,

368
00:14:49,370 --> 00:14:50,760
call me directly.

369
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:52,750
Okay.

370
00:14:56,150 --> 00:14:57,030
Eat more.

371
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,110
What are you two chatting about?

372
00:14:59,110 --> 00:15:00,170
Just random stuff.

373
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:08,760
What's wrong?

374
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:10,150
Nothing.

375
00:15:10,150 --> 00:15:12,280
Just chatting about things back home.

376
00:15:12,910 --> 00:15:13,630
Eat more.

377
00:15:15,790 --> 00:15:17,450
Let me take you to the station.

378
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:18,280
No need.

379
00:15:18,300 --> 00:15:19,620
Just focus on your classes.

380
00:15:19,620 --> 00:15:20,510
Tell me honestly—

381
00:15:20,510 --> 00:15:21,360
when I went to buy drinks,

382
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:23,090
did my dad say something to you?

383
00:15:23,150 --> 00:15:23,910
We were having a good time.

384
00:15:23,910 --> 00:15:25,150
Why are you leaving all of a sudden?

385
00:15:25,150 --> 00:15:26,670
He didn't say anything.

386
00:15:28,680 --> 00:15:29,470
For real?

387
00:15:29,880 --> 00:15:30,410
For real.

388
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:33,320
Then why are you leaving?

389
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:35,580
Didn't you say you'd stay a few more days?

390
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:40,310
Because I don't want to
just spend these few days with you.

391
00:15:40,310 --> 00:15:41,910
I want to be with you forever.

392
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:45,030
So I have to go back

393
00:15:45,310 --> 00:15:46,770
to prepare for our future.

394
00:15:52,150 --> 00:15:53,150
But I don't know

395
00:15:53,150 --> 00:15:54,950
when we'll see each other again.

396
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:56,670
There are still so many places in Shanghai

397
00:15:56,670 --> 00:15:57,800
I haven't shown you.

398
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:04,120
It's okay. As long as I get to see you,
this trip to Shanghai is enough.

399
00:16:20,470 --> 00:16:22,870
Alright, go back to class. I'm leaving.

400
00:16:24,080 --> 00:16:24,770
Go on.

401
00:16:39,390 --> 00:16:40,790
Ladies and gentlemen,

402
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,260
we are arriving at Shanhaiguan Station!

403
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:46,510
Passengers disembarking,
please take your belongings

404
00:16:46,510 --> 00:16:48,310
and get ready to leave the train!

405
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:49,790
Almost there. I need to grab a spot.

406
00:16:49,790 --> 00:16:50,620
Young man.

407
00:16:51,390 --> 00:16:52,670
What's in that drawing?

408
00:16:52,670 --> 00:16:54,420
You've looked at it several times.

409
00:16:54,420 --> 00:16:56,260
It's a drawing of our plant.

410
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:58,850
-Hey, watch it.
-I'm sorry.

411
00:17:00,270 --> 00:17:01,470
Finally found a spot.

412
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:06,720
Young man.

413
00:17:08,349 --> 00:17:09,550
You're pretty young.

414
00:17:13,310 --> 00:17:15,040
It's not a holiday or anything.

415
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:18,079
Is it easy to take time off
from university?

416
00:17:20,020 --> 00:17:21,240
I-I'm not a university student.

417
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:22,750
I came to visit friends.

418
00:17:24,359 --> 00:17:25,069
I'm sorry.

419
00:17:26,030 --> 00:17:27,490
Now that you mention it...

420
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:29,890
you really don't look like one.

421
00:17:34,550 --> 00:17:36,080
This drawing is quite nice.

422
00:17:36,250 --> 00:17:37,980
My girlfriend drew this for me.

423
00:17:38,740 --> 00:17:39,640
Your girlfriend drew this?

424
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:40,160
Yeah.

425
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:42,720
She's really good.

426
00:17:44,310 --> 00:17:45,720
She's a college student, right?

427
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:46,240
Yeah.

428
00:17:47,070 --> 00:17:51,680
She studies architecture
at Shanghai... Tongzhou University.

429
00:17:52,830 --> 00:17:53,720
Impressive!

430
00:17:54,070 --> 00:17:55,550
Shanghai Tongzhou University—

431
00:17:55,550 --> 00:17:57,010
that's really something!

432
00:17:57,030 --> 00:17:58,880
That university is amazing.

433
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:01,840
They say graduates from there

434
00:18:02,030 --> 00:18:03,720
are highly sought after in the job market.

435
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:04,320
Is that so?

436
00:18:04,330 --> 00:18:05,260
You're screwed.

437
00:18:05,310 --> 00:18:06,130
She's definitely

438
00:18:06,130 --> 00:18:07,730
going to settle in Shanghai.

439
00:18:08,310 --> 00:18:09,640
What are you going to do?

440
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:14,350
Alright, alright, you sit tight.

441
00:18:14,350 --> 00:18:15,000
Just sit.

442
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:15,880
I gotta get off.

443
00:18:16,260 --> 00:18:17,020
Okay, okay.

444
00:18:35,890 --> 00:18:36,520
Mr. Ding.

445
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,860
I-I've been thinking lately.

446
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:40,750
Well, I'm thinking of

447
00:18:40,750 --> 00:18:41,750
going to Shanghai to find work.

448
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:43,480
Do you think that's a good path?

449
00:18:44,350 --> 00:18:45,550
What can you do there?

450
00:18:47,430 --> 00:18:49,360
Haul sacks on a construction site?

451
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:51,740
Enduring hardship isn't a skill.

452
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,510
Young people are all the same.

453
00:18:54,510 --> 00:18:55,590
I was young once, too.

454
00:18:55,590 --> 00:18:56,790
I've been there.

455
00:18:57,510 --> 00:18:58,770
What you're saying...

456
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:00,600
Don't you want to give...

457
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:03,200
give Xiaodan a—what do you call it?

458
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:04,960
A happy and stable life?

459
00:19:05,670 --> 00:19:06,540
Of course I do.

460
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:08,840
Go to technical school then.

461
00:19:08,970 --> 00:19:10,000
Turning, fitting, milling,
planing, and welding—

462
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:12,660
master just one,
and you'll never be out of work.

463
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:14,680
The technical school's already
started its term.

464
00:19:14,680 --> 00:19:16,410
How am I supposed to enroll now?

465
00:19:17,510 --> 00:19:20,110
Tell me.
What did you do with Xiaoman this time?

466
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:23,200
He came to Shanghai to find me.

467
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:26,110
Like a dream... It feels like a dream.

468
00:19:26,110 --> 00:19:27,350
And a sweet one.

469
00:19:27,590 --> 00:19:29,590
Do you know what the best part
of a sweet dream is?

470
00:19:29,590 --> 00:19:31,400
It's when it comes true!

471
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:32,750
I know.

472
00:19:35,110 --> 00:19:36,350
Look how happy you are.

473
00:19:36,350 --> 00:19:38,880
I could tell you liked him
back in high school.

474
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,730
Who was it that kept denying it?

475
00:19:41,110 --> 00:19:43,000
Really? Did I deny it?

476
00:19:43,310 --> 00:19:45,310
I guess... I guess that did happen.

477
00:19:46,130 --> 00:19:46,750
But back then,

478
00:19:46,750 --> 00:19:48,610
didn't the teachers always think

479
00:19:48,960 --> 00:19:50,550
you and Xia Lei were together?

480
00:19:50,550 --> 00:19:51,200
Exactly.

481
00:19:52,510 --> 00:19:53,720
We got called to the office

482
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:55,000
because of some cheating incident.

483
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,590
Then, out of nowhere, the teacher asked,

484
00:19:56,590 --> 00:19:57,880
"Are you two dating?"

485
00:19:58,640 --> 00:19:59,770
Gave me such a fright.

486
00:19:59,770 --> 00:20:01,970
I was so afraid of being misunderstood.

487
00:20:03,350 --> 00:20:03,950
By the way,

488
00:20:04,540 --> 00:20:05,430
I remember...

489
00:20:05,550 --> 00:20:08,720
isn't your school
quite close to Xia Lei's?

490
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:11,590
It'd be so convenient for you two
to look out for each other.

491
00:20:11,590 --> 00:20:12,790
Why not consider him?

492
00:20:13,110 --> 00:20:15,380
We were desk mates in high school.

493
00:20:15,930 --> 00:20:18,200
If I were interested,
it would've happened ages ago.

494
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:19,800
It was never going to happen.

495
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:21,750
Why...

496
00:20:23,110 --> 00:20:24,640
don't you like him?

497
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:27,050
He was a top student.
First in the whole school.

498
00:20:27,050 --> 00:20:28,690
Then why don't you like him?

499
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,880
Didn't you grow up together?

500
00:20:32,750 --> 00:20:33,470
True.

501
00:20:33,590 --> 00:20:35,440
You need to like the person,

502
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:37,430
not a class ranking.

503
00:20:38,350 --> 00:20:39,540
Xiaoman was dead last,

504
00:20:39,540 --> 00:20:41,200
but I still like him, right?

505
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,000
Xia Lei...

506
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:49,480
My impression of him is that...

507
00:20:50,550 --> 00:20:52,610
he's always been preparing for exams

508
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,330
and rushing somewhere,

509
00:20:54,660 --> 00:20:56,660
but I never knew where he was headed.

510
00:20:57,080 --> 00:20:57,830
And I always felt

511
00:20:57,830 --> 00:20:59,640
he didn't know where he was headed either.

512
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:00,160
So...

513
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:02,690
what is there to like about him?

514
00:21:04,860 --> 00:21:05,940
That makes sense.

515
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:08,320
What do you think of Xiaoman?

516
00:21:08,590 --> 00:21:09,310
Xiaoman?

517
00:21:10,350 --> 00:21:11,410
Just like his name,

518
00:21:11,960 --> 00:21:13,000
the little East Chemical Plant

519
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,800
is enough to satisfy
all his expectations in life.

520
00:21:19,310 --> 00:21:20,110
What about me?

521
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:22,270
You?

522
00:21:25,110 --> 00:21:26,350
You...

523
00:21:28,270 --> 00:21:29,330
are pretty fickle.

524
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:31,750
Me? Fickle?

525
00:21:32,070 --> 00:21:33,880
I don't mean romantically.

526
00:21:34,750 --> 00:21:37,480
I think you're pretty fickle
toward the world.

527
00:21:38,220 --> 00:21:40,160
But it's exactly because of
that "fickleness"

528
00:21:40,160 --> 00:21:42,420
that you can always pursue what you want.

529
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:49,930
Director Liu.

530
00:21:50,650 --> 00:21:52,350
Well, how did you two end up
coming here together?

531
00:21:52,350 --> 00:21:53,150
Go have a seat.

532
00:21:54,850 --> 00:21:55,880
We

533
00:21:56,470 --> 00:21:58,320
came today about Xiaoman.

534
00:21:58,350 --> 00:22:01,080
We were hoping
you could help get him into school.

535
00:22:02,020 --> 00:22:04,550
For enrollment,
you need to talk to the school.

536
00:22:04,550 --> 00:22:05,720
True, but...

537
00:22:05,750 --> 00:22:07,750
we thought if the organization could
put in a word,

538
00:22:07,750 --> 00:22:09,810
it would be easier to get things done.

539
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:11,530
Dr. Tong,

540
00:22:11,960 --> 00:22:13,000
I just

541
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:14,660
push papers in the office now.

542
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:17,150
I really have no influence
over the school.

543
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:18,440
Besides,

544
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:22,090
the organization can't
take care of everything, can it?

545
00:22:23,110 --> 00:22:25,350
But Xiaoman is a good kid.

546
00:22:25,490 --> 00:22:27,910
He was retaliated against
for doing a good deed.

547
00:22:27,910 --> 00:22:29,540
That Feng Xiaobo he hit—

548
00:22:30,150 --> 00:22:31,490
he's a little thug.

549
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:33,200
He did it to protect himself

550
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:33,900
and his classmates.

551
00:22:33,900 --> 00:22:35,140
It was self-defense.

552
00:22:35,350 --> 00:22:37,590
I know all that.

553
00:22:38,310 --> 00:22:38,790
But...

554
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:40,020
Then tell me,

555
00:22:40,050 --> 00:22:41,550
if he can't get into technical school

556
00:22:41,550 --> 00:22:42,880
b-because of this,

557
00:22:43,140 --> 00:22:44,580
he can't become a worker.

558
00:22:44,750 --> 00:22:46,200
Then he won't have a job.

559
00:22:46,260 --> 00:22:46,920
And without a job,

560
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:49,720
won't his whole life be finished
before it starts?

561
00:22:50,590 --> 00:22:53,110
I understand everything you're saying.

562
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:55,640
We all watched

563
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:57,350
Xiaoman grow up.

564
00:22:57,350 --> 00:22:57,750
Yes.

565
00:22:58,200 --> 00:22:59,240
Back then,

566
00:22:59,310 --> 00:23:01,000
when his grandma ran that newsstand,

567
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:03,000
I was the one who helped apply for it.

568
00:23:03,110 --> 00:23:06,640
And that year
at the plant anniversary celebration,

569
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:08,610
he and that... what's his name... Sen?

570
00:23:08,610 --> 00:23:09,330
Zhuang Sen.

571
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:10,070
Right, right.

572
00:23:10,070 --> 00:23:12,200
They made a scene on stage,

573
00:23:12,350 --> 00:23:14,880
and I got dragged into trouble
for that later.

574
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:17,730
After his grandma passed away,

575
00:23:17,810 --> 00:23:19,880
I ran around taking care of everything

576
00:23:19,880 --> 00:23:21,310
I could for him.

577
00:23:22,790 --> 00:23:24,270
Okay, I know about

578
00:23:24,350 --> 00:23:25,200
this matter.

579
00:23:25,350 --> 00:23:26,530
I'll report it to the leadership,

580
00:23:26,530 --> 00:23:27,350
and we'll discuss it in a meeting...

581
00:23:27,350 --> 00:23:28,350
Alright, alright, Liu.

582
00:23:28,350 --> 00:23:29,660
Spare me this "report and discuss"

583
00:23:29,660 --> 00:23:31,120
bureaucratic runaround.

584
00:23:31,750 --> 00:23:32,790
What's the use of
spouting that useless crap?

585
00:23:32,790 --> 00:23:34,640
What? Is this our first day here?

586
00:23:35,590 --> 00:23:37,270
Every time you officials
start talking like that,

587
00:23:37,270 --> 00:23:39,360
the plant just waits for your meetings.

588
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:40,070
The plant can wait for your meetings,

589
00:23:40,070 --> 00:23:41,350
but can Xiaoman wait for it?

590
00:23:41,350 --> 00:23:43,000
No, Ding, stop getting so agitated.

591
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,200
We... we're just discussing this...

592
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:44,750
Who's agitated?

593
00:23:44,750 --> 00:23:45,590
Since I came in, entering the room,

594
00:23:45,590 --> 00:23:46,640
did I say a word?

595
00:23:46,750 --> 00:23:48,350
Wasn't it you who wound me up?

596
00:23:48,630 --> 00:23:51,070
Always talking about the good deeds
you've done.

597
00:23:51,070 --> 00:23:52,590
What, afraid we won't know?

598
00:23:52,590 --> 00:23:53,660
Only talking about the good parts!

599
00:23:53,660 --> 00:23:55,400
Well, if I don't say it, you won't know.

600
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:55,880
Listen up—

601
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:57,720
frankly, who's to blame
for Xiaoman's situation?

602
00:23:57,720 --> 00:23:59,980
It's our plant's fault, I'm telling you!

603
00:24:00,590 --> 00:24:02,590
If only the plant had
had effective management measures

604
00:24:02,590 --> 00:24:03,590
and been a bit stricter,

605
00:24:03,590 --> 00:24:04,160
don't you agree?

606
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:06,750
If the plant had implemented
more effective measures across the board,

607
00:24:06,750 --> 00:24:08,750
would Xiaoman—a mere kid,

608
00:24:08,750 --> 00:24:09,720
a little brat—

609
00:24:09,750 --> 00:24:11,950
have needed to report
that gas station?

610
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:14,000
Would he have ended up
in juvenile detention?

611
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,550
Would he have lost his schooling?

612
00:24:15,550 --> 00:24:16,750
Don't you have a clue?

613
00:24:16,750 --> 00:24:18,290
Ding, I don't like hearing you say that.

614
00:24:18,290 --> 00:24:19,310
So what if you don't like it?

615
00:24:19,310 --> 00:24:19,590
Well,

616
00:24:19,590 --> 00:24:21,350
Director Meng stepped in back then!

617
00:24:21,350 --> 00:24:22,880
I wasn't afraid to slap him in the face
back then,

618
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:24,540
and I'm not afraid to do it now!

619
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:27,730
He could step in back then,
so why can't he now?

620
00:24:28,130 --> 00:24:29,730
Fine! I won't argue with you.

621
00:24:30,130 --> 00:24:31,930
Always waving your arms around.

622
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:34,310
Dr. Tong,

623
00:24:34,590 --> 00:24:35,850
here's the situation:

624
00:24:35,880 --> 00:24:39,000
now, the school and the hospital

625
00:24:39,070 --> 00:24:41,670
are gradually being separated
from the plant.

626
00:24:41,750 --> 00:24:43,070
The technical school now

627
00:24:43,070 --> 00:24:45,000
falls under the local education bureau.

628
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:46,750
We don't have a say anymore.

629
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:53,590
Then just let Xiaoman
come back to work here!

630
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:54,680
Listen up,

631
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:56,310
you have to find a future for him.

632
00:24:56,310 --> 00:24:57,960
Right. You have to help him.

633
00:24:58,590 --> 00:24:59,050
Well...

634
00:24:59,550 --> 00:25:02,000
H-How am I supposed to find one for him?

635
00:25:04,310 --> 00:25:05,440
Don't glare at me.

636
00:25:05,510 --> 00:25:06,920
I just remembered something.

637
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:10,750
The technical school is
under local management now,

638
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:14,110
but Principal Jin of the school

639
00:25:14,110 --> 00:25:15,550
came from our plant.

640
00:25:15,550 --> 00:25:16,640
Who? Jin Fu?

641
00:25:17,070 --> 00:25:18,070
It's "Jin Changfu."

642
00:25:18,070 --> 00:25:18,750
Jin Changfu.

643
00:25:18,750 --> 00:25:20,400
Right. So here's what you do—

644
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:22,070
find Principal Jin.

645
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:24,270
As long as the technical school
agrees to accept Xiaoman,

646
00:25:24,270 --> 00:25:25,510
the organization will

647
00:25:25,510 --> 00:25:28,350
give you its full cooperation on
everything else. Okay?

648
00:25:28,350 --> 00:25:29,500
Does your word count?

649
00:25:29,500 --> 00:25:30,630
Of course it counts.

650
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:31,790
Come on, Tong Guizhen, let's go.

651
00:25:31,790 --> 00:25:32,350
I'll handle this.

652
00:25:32,350 --> 00:25:32,880
Don't waste time with him.

653
00:25:32,880 --> 00:25:34,740
It's useless. Let's go. Let's go.

654
00:25:37,070 --> 00:25:37,750
You downed it in one go.

655
00:25:37,750 --> 00:25:39,750
My senior can still hold his liquor.

656
00:25:40,680 --> 00:25:41,410
Put it there.

657
00:25:41,750 --> 00:25:42,400
I'll pour myself.

658
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:43,550
Good baijiu. Saved it for years.

659
00:25:43,550 --> 00:25:44,720
We never had the heart to drink it.

660
00:25:44,720 --> 00:25:45,590
Senior, you are so hospitable.

661
00:25:45,590 --> 00:25:46,200
So hospitable.

662
00:25:46,200 --> 00:25:46,960
-Yes.
-So hospitable.

663
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:48,350
-Drink more.
-You go open

664
00:25:48,350 --> 00:25:48,750
that bottle.

665
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:49,590
-No, no, no.
-Okay!

666
00:25:49,590 --> 00:25:50,680
T-There's more here!

667
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:51,750
No, no. Enough, enough.

668
00:25:51,750 --> 00:25:52,530
I really appreciate it!

669
00:25:52,530 --> 00:25:53,350
We'll buy more if there's none left.

670
00:25:53,350 --> 00:25:54,000
We'll go buy more.

671
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:54,860
Keep drinking.

672
00:25:54,960 --> 00:25:56,420
-We're happy today.
-Yes.

673
00:25:56,510 --> 00:25:58,070
You've made something of yourself now.

674
00:25:58,070 --> 00:26:00,330
We haven't seen each other in a long time.

675
00:26:00,510 --> 00:26:01,310
Do you remember

676
00:26:01,310 --> 00:26:04,110
when you were...
still a worker in the plant back then?

677
00:26:04,110 --> 00:26:04,680
That time,

678
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:07,750
didn't you get into a fight with thieves?

679
00:26:07,750 --> 00:26:09,130
-Yeah.
-He was so rash!

680
00:26:09,160 --> 00:26:10,880
That was... He was truly young.

681
00:26:10,880 --> 00:26:11,750
As fearless as a newborn calf!

682
00:26:11,750 --> 00:26:12,350
He went out alone

683
00:26:12,350 --> 00:26:14,210
and took on three guys by himself.

684
00:26:14,350 --> 00:26:15,410
One against three!

685
00:26:15,920 --> 00:26:16,750
Good for you.

686
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:18,200
But frankly speaking,

687
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:20,050
if I, your senior, hadn't stepped in,

688
00:26:20,050 --> 00:26:20,920
if I hadn't acted,

689
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:21,590
if I hadn't helped,

690
00:26:21,590 --> 00:26:22,590
your two hands—

691
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:25,200
let's be honest—
wouldn't you have lost them?

692
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:25,550
Right, right.

693
00:26:25,550 --> 00:26:26,830
You'd have been left with
just two stumps, right?

694
00:26:26,830 --> 00:26:28,160
What are you saying?

695
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:29,030
True story!

696
00:26:29,070 --> 00:26:29,960
That's true?

697
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:30,960
Really. Really.

698
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:31,830
I owe

699
00:26:32,110 --> 00:26:33,310
my life to my senior.

700
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:37,200
But about Xiaoman's situation...

701
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:38,330
What about Xiaoman?

702
00:26:39,350 --> 00:26:40,860
What's wrong? What's wrong with Xiaoman?

703
00:26:40,860 --> 00:26:41,390
Exactly.

704
00:26:42,350 --> 00:26:43,200
In a sense,

705
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:44,520
isn't he just like you?

706
00:26:44,540 --> 00:26:46,540
When he saw someone being bullied

707
00:26:47,350 --> 00:26:49,750
and the country's interests being harmed,

708
00:26:49,960 --> 00:26:51,920
he rushed in without a second thought!

709
00:26:51,920 --> 00:26:54,160
Back in the day, y-you were awarded

710
00:26:54,160 --> 00:26:55,720
the "Heroic Citizen," right?

711
00:26:55,720 --> 00:26:56,850
What about Xiaoman?

712
00:26:57,720 --> 00:26:58,350
Fine.

713
00:26:58,960 --> 00:27:00,400
We accept that we get nothing.

714
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:01,590
We accept it with no complaints.

715
00:27:01,590 --> 00:27:03,500
But how can you deny him his schooling
over this?

716
00:27:03,500 --> 00:27:05,430
Exactly. Look what a good kid he is.

717
00:27:05,590 --> 00:27:06,440
Everyone at the plant says

718
00:27:06,440 --> 00:27:07,570
Xiaoman is a good kid

719
00:27:07,590 --> 00:27:08,590
whenever he's mentioned.

720
00:27:08,590 --> 00:27:10,240
Yes, right!

721
00:27:10,260 --> 00:27:12,700
However... the school rules

722
00:27:12,730 --> 00:27:14,090
are set in stone.

723
00:27:14,120 --> 00:27:14,650
No, wait.

724
00:27:19,590 --> 00:27:20,910
Slow down, Senior.

725
00:27:20,930 --> 00:27:21,930
Jin.

726
00:27:23,440 --> 00:27:24,110
Right.

727
00:27:25,350 --> 00:27:28,240
You're now the principal
of the technical school.

728
00:27:30,960 --> 00:27:32,760
So what if you're the principal?

729
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:35,580
You don't care about
your fellow workers anymore?

730
00:27:35,580 --> 00:27:36,350
Senior...

731
00:27:36,750 --> 00:27:38,350
Your status rises, your vision rises,

732
00:27:38,350 --> 00:27:39,810
and ours stays low, is that it?

733
00:27:39,810 --> 00:27:40,350
How could that be?

734
00:27:40,350 --> 00:27:42,070
Senior, what are you saying?

735
00:27:42,660 --> 00:27:45,200
Well, it's precisely because
I'm the principal

736
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:47,200
that I can't break the rules,

737
00:27:47,310 --> 00:27:48,000
right?

738
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:48,960
The key issue is

739
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:51,310
that Xiaoman didn't take
the college entrance exam.

740
00:27:51,310 --> 00:27:53,510
He has no student registration
and no scores.

741
00:27:53,510 --> 00:27:55,920
How can I let him enroll directly
without the exam?

742
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:56,750
For that,

743
00:27:56,750 --> 00:28:00,410
he'll probably have to wait
until next year to take the exam again.

744
00:28:00,440 --> 00:28:01,520
Can we do this?

745
00:28:04,310 --> 00:28:05,640
See if this is possible.

746
00:28:05,880 --> 00:28:06,920
As the principal,

747
00:28:08,350 --> 00:28:10,750
could you allow a student
to audit classes?

748
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:12,200
That's possible.

749
00:28:12,590 --> 00:28:13,660
Then, as the principal,

750
00:28:13,660 --> 00:28:15,860
can you let a student skip a grade?

751
00:28:16,710 --> 00:28:17,970
That's also possible.

752
00:28:18,170 --> 00:28:20,560
Exactly. Plenty of students skip grades.

753
00:28:20,890 --> 00:28:21,560
No problem.

754
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:22,750
Alright then.

755
00:28:22,750 --> 00:28:24,080
I'll have a drink first.

756
00:28:25,750 --> 00:28:26,590
Slow down.

757
00:28:27,490 --> 00:28:28,620
You'll choke again.

758
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:33,660
You always down it in one gulp.

759
00:28:34,050 --> 00:28:35,310
Here's the situation.

760
00:28:37,150 --> 00:28:40,150
There is a student. He missed the exam.

761
00:28:41,350 --> 00:28:43,480
Let him audit classes first,

762
00:28:44,750 --> 00:28:48,270
then take the entrance exam next year.

763
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:49,830
If he passes,

764
00:28:50,590 --> 00:28:53,190
let him skip to the second year.
How about that?

765
00:28:54,030 --> 00:28:55,490
Let me think it through...

766
00:29:00,200 --> 00:29:01,260
That's a good idea.

767
00:29:01,350 --> 00:29:02,470
That's why you're my senior!

768
00:29:02,470 --> 00:29:04,000
You really have a lot of ideas!

769
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:04,680
See?

770
00:29:05,750 --> 00:29:06,410
This works.

771
00:29:07,400 --> 00:29:09,450
I've always had a rigid mind.

772
00:29:09,880 --> 00:29:11,000
That's our Ding for you!

773
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:12,200
Come on!

774
00:29:12,620 --> 00:29:13,250
It's settled?

775
00:29:13,250 --> 00:29:14,750
Let me pour you some. Have some.

776
00:29:14,750 --> 00:29:16,720
-Here.
-Don't drink too much.

777
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:17,750
No more words.

778
00:29:18,300 --> 00:29:20,630
We're real brothers. Bottoms up!

779
00:29:20,650 --> 00:29:21,850
Slow down. Slow down.

780
00:29:25,310 --> 00:29:26,510
You're a true friend.

781
00:29:26,680 --> 00:29:27,610
My good brother.

782
00:29:27,720 --> 00:29:29,200
Don't worry. For our factory's children,

783
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,660
schooling is guaranteed.

784
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:33,370
You should've been
Party Secretary long ago!

785
00:29:35,750 --> 00:29:38,080
We thank you
from the bottom of our hearts.

786
00:29:38,110 --> 00:29:40,240
Xiaoman, today you've got to tell me.

787
00:29:40,260 --> 00:29:42,180
I heard you were holding a knife then,

788
00:29:42,180 --> 00:29:43,970
and with one stab, you pierced

789
00:29:44,310 --> 00:29:45,640
Feng Xiaobo's stomach.

790
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:47,310
When he was running down the street,

791
00:29:47,310 --> 00:29:49,240
his intestines were spilling out.

792
00:29:50,110 --> 00:29:53,370
He was just holding them
while running all over the street.

793
00:29:54,110 --> 00:29:56,110
Is that true? Man, you're fierce.

794
00:29:56,440 --> 00:29:58,240
I really admire people like you.

795
00:29:58,480 --> 00:30:00,610
What are you on about? That's not true.

796
00:30:01,110 --> 00:30:03,160
But I don't regret it.

797
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:05,410
Regret wouldn't change anything.

798
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:07,080
Do you remember Sun Lulu?

799
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:08,990
What about her?

800
00:30:08,990 --> 00:30:10,520
We're really together now!

801
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:13,110
Thanks to the letter

802
00:30:13,110 --> 00:30:14,550
you wrote for me back then.

803
00:30:14,550 --> 00:30:17,240
If not for you, neither of us
would've said anything first—

804
00:30:17,240 --> 00:30:19,770
who knows
how long we would've dragged it out?

805
00:30:21,240 --> 00:30:22,240
Sun Lulu...

806
00:30:28,270 --> 00:30:29,130
Treat her well.

807
00:30:29,370 --> 00:30:30,070
Treat her well.

808
00:30:30,070 --> 00:30:30,530
Will do.

809
00:30:34,200 --> 00:30:35,310
Attention, everyone.

810
00:30:35,310 --> 00:30:37,710
We're having class in this workshop today.

811
00:30:37,720 --> 00:30:39,320
There are tools everywhere.

812
00:30:39,790 --> 00:30:41,480
Don't touch any tools

813
00:30:41,480 --> 00:30:43,030
unrelated to your studies. Understood?

814
00:30:43,030 --> 00:30:44,630
-Understood!
-Understood!

815
00:30:44,650 --> 00:30:46,260
Last time, I went over

816
00:30:46,490 --> 00:30:48,000
the safety precautions for welding.

817
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:48,880
Do you all remember them?

818
00:30:48,880 --> 00:30:50,000
-Yes.
-Yes.

819
00:30:50,070 --> 00:30:51,190
You should remember them well.

820
00:30:51,190 --> 00:30:54,050
I don't care whether you become
good welders or not,

821
00:30:54,270 --> 00:30:56,720
but you must remember
the safety precautions.

822
00:30:56,720 --> 00:30:57,880
I'm not joking.

823
00:30:58,310 --> 00:30:59,440
I had a student once.

824
00:30:59,940 --> 00:31:01,800
He didn't pay attention in class.

825
00:31:02,830 --> 00:31:04,760
Later on the job, he made a mistake.

826
00:31:05,600 --> 00:31:07,730
He was electrocuted
while replacing the welding rod.

827
00:31:07,730 --> 00:31:09,660
Aren't welding gloves insulated?

828
00:31:09,880 --> 00:31:11,610
Welding gloves are insulated.

829
00:31:12,040 --> 00:31:13,760
But he sweated through them.

830
00:31:14,440 --> 00:31:16,970
The electrode holder
jolted him off his feet,

831
00:31:17,830 --> 00:31:19,880
and he landed right back on it.

832
00:31:20,180 --> 00:31:21,880
As a result, electricity went through
his whole body.

833
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:23,540
And he was gone just like that!

834
00:31:24,070 --> 00:31:25,400
I had another student.

835
00:31:25,880 --> 00:31:27,880
Because he didn't check the surroundings,

836
00:31:27,880 --> 00:31:30,080
some molten slag fell to the floor below

837
00:31:30,200 --> 00:31:31,880
and set it on fire.

838
00:31:32,310 --> 00:31:33,720
He was trapped upstairs

839
00:31:34,270 --> 00:31:35,720
and burned alive!

840
00:31:36,640 --> 00:31:37,900
So you must be careful!

841
00:31:39,270 --> 00:31:40,680
And I had yet another student.

842
00:31:40,680 --> 00:31:43,080
He was careless
when changing the gas tank.

843
00:31:43,110 --> 00:31:44,110
It exploded.

844
00:31:44,790 --> 00:31:46,920
You all know how powerful a gas tank is!

845
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:49,160
He was blown to pieces!

846
00:31:49,940 --> 00:31:51,470
You can imagine that scene.

847
00:31:52,010 --> 00:31:54,730
Mr. Teng, was your master
Old Heretic Huang?

848
00:31:56,160 --> 00:31:58,360
Was your master Old Heretic Huang?

849
00:31:58,440 --> 00:31:59,900
You are Old Heretic Huang!

850
00:32:00,030 --> 00:32:01,880
From what you've just said yourself,
aren't you basically the same?

851
00:32:01,880 --> 00:32:04,610
Your students are
like Old Heretic Huang's disciples—

852
00:32:04,610 --> 00:32:06,210
hardly any of them survived.

853
00:32:09,840 --> 00:32:11,270
Believe it or not.

854
00:32:11,440 --> 00:32:12,370
I'm telling you,

855
00:32:12,540 --> 00:32:15,850
if you don't believe me...
feel free to keep spacing out.

856
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:17,110
Watch closely!

857
00:32:17,300 --> 00:32:18,000
-Okay.
-Okay.

858
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:18,570
Okay.

859
00:32:26,030 --> 00:32:28,750
This is one of those trulli in Italy.

860
00:32:29,110 --> 00:32:29,720
Beautiful, isn't it?

861
00:32:29,720 --> 00:32:31,000
-It's beautiful.
-Very nice.

862
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:32,000
Very nice.

863
00:32:32,270 --> 00:32:33,480
I took these
after the college entrance exam

864
00:32:33,480 --> 00:32:34,740
when I went traveling.

865
00:32:34,740 --> 00:32:35,880
I've got plenty more.

866
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:37,480
Is this Alberobello in Italy—

867
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:38,790
the "Paradise Town"?

868
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:40,030
I read somewhere

869
00:32:40,030 --> 00:32:43,130
that there are thousands of
these stone-roofed houses left there.

870
00:32:43,130 --> 00:32:44,440
It's so beautiful.

871
00:32:44,740 --> 00:32:46,110
Your photo looks even better
than the reference material.

872
00:32:46,110 --> 00:32:47,270
That's straight from the source.

873
00:32:47,270 --> 00:32:47,960
You like it?

874
00:32:47,960 --> 00:32:49,000
It really is well taken.

875
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:50,200
I'll print a set for you.

876
00:32:50,200 --> 00:32:51,480
Sure. Thanks.

877
00:32:54,880 --> 00:32:55,720
This is a stone house

878
00:32:55,720 --> 00:32:57,380
in the town of Yvoire, France.

879
00:32:57,580 --> 00:32:59,110
I went there in high school.

880
00:32:59,310 --> 00:33:00,480
But at that time,

881
00:33:00,830 --> 00:33:03,000
I didn't take proper photos
or keep records.

882
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:04,680
All I took were tourist snapshots.

883
00:33:04,680 --> 00:33:05,980
They were completely useless.

884
00:33:05,980 --> 00:33:07,640
-That's a pity.
-What a shame.

885
00:33:08,310 --> 00:33:09,680
But I didn't go inside this stone house.

886
00:33:09,680 --> 00:33:10,410
Did you go in?

887
00:33:10,680 --> 00:33:12,790
No. It was under protection when I went.

888
00:33:12,790 --> 00:33:16,030
But I went to that one. Wait a second.

889
00:33:21,070 --> 00:33:21,750
This looks nice.

890
00:33:21,750 --> 00:33:22,790
This place is really beautiful!

891
00:33:22,790 --> 00:33:23,310
You've been there?

892
00:33:23,310 --> 00:33:24,110
I haven't.

893
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:26,510
Have you been inside this one?

894
00:33:26,510 --> 00:33:27,110
No.

895
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:29,230
I remember it was really cool inside.

896
00:33:29,300 --> 00:33:31,140
And on the dining table inside,

897
00:33:31,170 --> 00:33:33,370
there was a 14th-century candlestick.

898
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:35,110
A 14th-century candlestick?

899
00:33:35,110 --> 00:33:35,790
Xiaodan?

900
00:33:36,270 --> 00:33:38,330
You really should go see it sometime.

901
00:33:40,270 --> 00:33:41,720
Bro, stop working out.

902
00:33:42,030 --> 00:33:44,110
The more you exercise, the hungrier I get.

903
00:33:44,110 --> 00:33:45,270
If I burn a few more calories now,

904
00:33:45,270 --> 00:33:46,800
I can eat more later, right?

905
00:33:51,110 --> 00:33:51,880
What took you so long?

906
00:33:51,880 --> 00:33:53,140
Let's go. Let's go eat.

907
00:33:53,500 --> 00:33:55,300
I'm not going. You guys go ahead.

908
00:33:55,310 --> 00:33:56,270
Why not?

909
00:33:57,790 --> 00:33:59,310
I'm going to
the hometown association gathering.

910
00:33:59,310 --> 00:34:01,440
I want to get to know people
from my hometown.

911
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:03,680
You should've said that earlier—
we've been waiting for you.

912
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:05,670
Bring back some goodies
after the gathering.

913
00:34:05,670 --> 00:34:06,260
Sure.

914
00:34:07,070 --> 00:34:08,270
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

915
00:34:12,420 --> 00:34:14,050
This one... He is, right?

916
00:34:14,710 --> 00:34:15,590
Hey, man.

917
00:34:15,840 --> 00:34:16,840
Is this
the hometown association gathering?

918
00:34:16,840 --> 00:34:17,880
Yes. You're here for it, right?

919
00:34:17,880 --> 00:34:18,670
Yes. I'm from Tiecheng.

920
00:34:18,670 --> 00:34:19,469
Right, right.

921
00:34:19,480 --> 00:34:20,190
We were just waiting for you.

922
00:34:20,190 --> 00:34:21,320
There's an empty seat here!

923
00:34:21,320 --> 00:34:21,880
Sit here.

924
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:22,960
I'll sit over there.

925
00:34:22,960 --> 00:34:23,710
Okay. Sit.

926
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:27,320
How about some beer?

927
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:27,800
Thanks.

928
00:34:28,670 --> 00:34:29,280
Take off your bag.

929
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:30,940
Everyone's pretty much here.

930
00:34:31,480 --> 00:34:32,480
Fellow townsmen,

931
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:34,400
hello everyone. You all know me, right?

932
00:34:34,400 --> 00:34:35,590
-Yes, we do!
-Yeah!

933
00:34:35,590 --> 00:34:37,670
I won't waste your time
introducing myself then.

934
00:34:37,670 --> 00:34:38,280
No need.

935
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:39,880
Who doesn't know you, Director Zheng?

936
00:34:39,880 --> 00:34:41,320
Exactly. Who doesn't know you?

937
00:34:41,320 --> 00:34:42,409
He's the third vice director
of the Student Union's

938
00:34:42,409 --> 00:34:43,670
External Relations Department—

939
00:34:43,670 --> 00:34:44,110
last name Zheng.

940
00:34:44,110 --> 00:34:46,320
Look at the environment
we're eating in today.

941
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:48,480
Doesn't it look like the peaks and ridges

942
00:34:48,480 --> 00:34:50,110
of our hometown?

943
00:34:50,190 --> 00:34:50,670
-It does!
-Yeah!

944
00:34:50,670 --> 00:34:52,480
They surround us tightly.

945
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:52,900
Exactly.

946
00:34:52,900 --> 00:34:54,460
Once we gather like this,

947
00:34:54,630 --> 00:34:56,710
doesn't that warmth from home
come right back?

948
00:34:56,710 --> 00:34:57,880
-It's back!
-It's back!

949
00:34:57,880 --> 00:34:59,030
-It's all back!
-Yeah!

950
00:34:59,030 --> 00:34:59,670
It's back!

951
00:34:59,670 --> 00:35:00,320
Since it's back,

952
00:35:00,320 --> 00:35:01,480
let's have a drink first!

953
00:35:01,480 --> 00:35:03,230
-Cheers!
-Bottoms up!

954
00:35:03,320 --> 00:35:03,800
Cheers!

955
00:35:06,230 --> 00:35:09,320
As they say, when fellow townspeople meet,
the feeling is something else.

956
00:35:09,320 --> 00:35:10,000
I propose

957
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:11,710
that our newer members

958
00:35:11,710 --> 00:35:13,760
introduce themselves

959
00:35:13,840 --> 00:35:15,110
in their hometown dialect. How about it?

960
00:35:15,110 --> 00:35:15,880
-Okay!
-Yeah!

961
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:17,540
Who wants to go first? Come on!

962
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:21,280
Hello, everyone!

963
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:22,440
I'm Zhao Zhiyong.

964
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:24,550
I'm from Beita!

965
00:35:25,150 --> 00:35:27,110
Anyone who treats me to
a bowl of cold noodles

966
00:35:27,110 --> 00:35:28,840
is my sworn brother for life!

967
00:35:28,840 --> 00:35:29,710
-Great!
-Yeah!

968
00:35:29,730 --> 00:35:30,600
I'll treat you!

969
00:35:35,030 --> 00:35:36,430
My name is Guan Shengnan.

970
00:35:36,670 --> 00:35:38,130
I'm from the countryside.

971
00:35:38,590 --> 00:35:40,920
I went to high school in Erdaogou Town.

972
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:42,760
Back home,

973
00:35:42,760 --> 00:35:44,670
we distinguish
between rural and urban areas.

974
00:35:44,670 --> 00:35:46,150
But we are in Shanghai now.

975
00:35:46,230 --> 00:35:47,110
We're all...

976
00:35:47,110 --> 00:35:47,550
Right.

977
00:35:47,630 --> 00:35:50,290
-From the countryside!
-From the countryside!

978
00:35:53,280 --> 00:35:54,960
Who's next?

979
00:35:55,550 --> 00:35:56,070
Uh...

980
00:35:57,480 --> 00:35:58,670
My name is Xia Lei.

981
00:35:58,920 --> 00:36:00,230
I can't speak the Tiecheng dialect.

982
00:36:00,230 --> 00:36:01,670
I'm from the East Chemical Plant.

983
00:36:01,670 --> 00:36:03,670
I'm studying
communication engineering here.

984
00:36:03,670 --> 00:36:04,960
-Good!
-Yeah!

985
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:06,160
-Welcome!
-Welcome!

986
00:36:09,320 --> 00:36:09,920
Buddy.

987
00:36:10,800 --> 00:36:11,880
You're from the East Chemical Plant?

988
00:36:11,880 --> 00:36:12,480
Yes.

989
00:36:13,320 --> 00:36:15,920
No wonder your outfit is so weird.

990
00:36:16,320 --> 00:36:18,360
It's normal for someone like you
not to speak

991
00:36:18,360 --> 00:36:19,620
our Tiecheng dialect.

992
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:23,470
After all, you claim to be from
the East Chemical Plant

993
00:36:24,070 --> 00:36:26,000
and never mention the region.

994
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:26,780
There he goes again.

995
00:36:26,780 --> 00:36:28,510
Alright, why start this again?

996
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:30,120
I think you're pretty weird!

997
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:31,780
He is from the East Chemical Plant.

998
00:36:31,780 --> 00:36:32,840
Why can't he say it?

999
00:36:34,570 --> 00:36:35,260
Hey there.

1000
00:36:36,070 --> 00:36:39,190
I think you look good today.

1001
00:36:39,510 --> 00:36:41,360
Right. It looks very nice!

1002
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:43,110
See? Our sister knows how to talk.

1003
00:36:43,110 --> 00:36:43,710
Right?

1004
00:36:44,030 --> 00:36:46,110
Suits are for formal occasions.

1005
00:36:46,190 --> 00:36:46,840
Right?

1006
00:36:46,840 --> 00:36:47,110
-Yes.
-Right!

1007
00:36:47,110 --> 00:36:49,070
That shows he takes our gathering
very seriously!

1008
00:36:49,070 --> 00:36:50,320
Yes, he values it!

1009
00:36:50,500 --> 00:36:51,340
My turn!

1010
00:36:52,030 --> 00:36:53,590
I'm Fan Weijie,

1011
00:36:54,110 --> 00:36:55,480
a sophomore majoring in finance!

1012
00:36:55,480 --> 00:36:57,480
I didn't get the chance
to hang out with you

1013
00:36:57,480 --> 00:36:58,610
in my freshman year.

1014
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:00,230
I've always regretted that!

1015
00:37:00,230 --> 00:37:01,880
I hope you fellow townsmen
will look out for me!

1016
00:37:01,880 --> 00:37:02,940
I'll drink to that!

1017
00:37:03,030 --> 00:37:03,480
Yeah.

1018
00:37:03,670 --> 00:37:04,480
Come on, we'll drink with you!

1019
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:06,510
-Come on!
-Bottoms up!

1020
00:37:07,070 --> 00:37:07,870
Wait a second.

1021
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:10,800
Where is your hometown?

1022
00:37:11,230 --> 00:37:14,030
Don't tell me
you're from East Chemical Plant too?

1023
00:37:14,230 --> 00:37:15,110
I grew up

1024
00:37:15,140 --> 00:37:17,270
in the same village as Director Zheng.

1025
00:37:17,630 --> 00:37:19,290
We were raised on millet rice.

1026
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:20,590
I've got more stories
than gray hairs in my beard.

1027
00:37:20,590 --> 00:37:21,390
What's wrong?

1028
00:37:21,670 --> 00:37:22,280
So...

1029
00:37:22,320 --> 00:37:24,440
does Director Zheng have to call you...

1030
00:37:24,440 --> 00:37:25,190
"Uncle"?

1031
00:37:27,320 --> 00:37:28,110
Nonsense!

1032
00:37:28,670 --> 00:37:29,800
Director Zheng

1033
00:37:29,920 --> 00:37:31,480
is from the city!

1034
00:37:31,480 --> 00:37:32,840
City, countryside—

1035
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:34,440
now that we're in Shanghai, we're all...

1036
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:36,280
-From the countryside!
-From the countryside!

1037
00:37:36,280 --> 00:37:38,030
All us country folk, let's drink together!

1038
00:37:38,030 --> 00:37:38,670
Come on!

1039
00:37:38,670 --> 00:37:39,110
Bottoms up!

1040
00:37:39,110 --> 00:37:40,170
To us country folk!

1041
00:37:40,670 --> 00:37:41,190
Come on. Cheers!

1042
00:37:41,190 --> 00:37:41,670
-Cheers!
-Yeah!

1043
00:37:41,670 --> 00:37:43,130
-Bottoms up!
-Bottoms up!

1044
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:47,230
Come on, everyone, dig in.

1045
00:37:47,230 --> 00:37:48,290
Eat while it's hot!

1046
00:37:50,320 --> 00:37:51,450
Thanks for earlier.

1047
00:37:51,630 --> 00:37:53,960
No big deal. We're from the same hometown.

1048
00:37:53,980 --> 00:37:55,390
But we can't blame him.

1049
00:37:55,410 --> 00:37:58,210
We're just different from the locals
in Shanghai.

1050
00:38:00,610 --> 00:38:02,900
Yeah, of course we're different.

1051
00:38:03,320 --> 00:38:04,670
You look quite tacky.

1052
00:38:06,220 --> 00:38:07,800
You said earlier

1053
00:38:07,800 --> 00:38:09,800
that I value this gathering,

1054
00:38:09,800 --> 00:38:11,190
and that's why I dressed like this.

1055
00:38:11,190 --> 00:38:12,280
I was trying to help you out.

1056
00:38:12,280 --> 00:38:13,230
Couldn't you tell?

1057
00:38:13,230 --> 00:38:14,320
You got it wrong.

1058
00:38:15,070 --> 00:38:16,710
Look at your outfit. It's so countrified.

1059
00:38:16,710 --> 00:38:18,310
Come on, stand up. Let me see.

1060
00:38:19,590 --> 00:38:20,590
How is my outfit countrified?

1061
00:38:20,590 --> 00:38:21,480
I wasn't wrong, was I?

1062
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:22,280
See that?

1063
00:38:22,320 --> 00:38:23,360
A belt with punched holes.

1064
00:38:23,360 --> 00:38:24,480
Look at that belt—so outdated.

1065
00:38:24,480 --> 00:38:25,840
It's even peeling.

1066
00:38:26,480 --> 00:38:27,320
So many holes.

1067
00:38:28,270 --> 00:38:30,530
That's not what a boss's belt looks like.

1068
00:38:31,480 --> 00:38:32,770
What kind of belt does a boss wear?

1069
00:38:32,770 --> 00:38:33,640
A boss's belt?

1070
00:38:34,970 --> 00:38:36,670
Come on, let me show you

1071
00:38:36,670 --> 00:38:38,330
what a boss's belt looks like.

1072
00:38:38,670 --> 00:38:40,510
This is a belt a boss would wear.

1073
00:38:40,670 --> 00:38:43,070
See this? Clean, neat.

1074
00:38:43,070 --> 00:38:43,920
It never peels.

1075
00:38:43,920 --> 00:38:45,380
One smooth pull—no holes.

1076
00:38:46,070 --> 00:38:47,800
What do you like to clip on your waist?

1077
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:48,670
My keychain.

1078
00:38:48,880 --> 00:38:49,810
Shanghai locals

1079
00:38:49,840 --> 00:38:52,110
clip on phone pouches, you know?

1080
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:55,920
You open it and slip your phone in—
so convenient!

1081
00:38:56,070 --> 00:38:57,550
Clip on this kind of belt

1082
00:38:57,630 --> 00:38:59,670
and wear this phone case.

1083
00:38:59,670 --> 00:39:01,480
Then who would say
you're a country bumpkin?

1084
00:39:01,480 --> 00:39:02,110
Right?

1085
00:39:03,070 --> 00:39:03,670
Well...

1086
00:39:03,670 --> 00:39:05,920
this kind of belt
must be expensive, right?

1087
00:39:05,920 --> 00:39:06,920
Of course.

1088
00:39:06,920 --> 00:39:08,150
In stores, yeah.

1089
00:39:08,480 --> 00:39:09,450
But I have a source.

1090
00:39:09,450 --> 00:39:11,380
I can get you top-grade knockoffs—

1091
00:39:11,480 --> 00:39:12,880
the best quality around.

1092
00:39:13,360 --> 00:39:14,480
And cheap. Want one?

1093
00:39:14,480 --> 00:39:15,570
Sure! Get me one.

1094
00:39:15,600 --> 00:39:16,860
Hold on. Wait a second.

1095
00:39:17,230 --> 00:39:20,430
Did you go around the dorms
selling leather shoes before?

1096
00:39:22,510 --> 00:39:23,110
Yeah.

1097
00:39:24,590 --> 00:39:25,920
Listen to me, everyone.

1098
00:39:25,920 --> 00:39:27,880
This guy is a scammer.

1099
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:29,590
The head of my dorm

1100
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:32,190
went to the Mianyang
hometown association gathering.

1101
00:39:32,190 --> 00:39:34,030
He told me he met a guy from his hometown

1102
00:39:34,030 --> 00:39:35,480
and bought a pair of

1103
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:37,630
Norrona leather shoes from him.

1104
00:39:38,320 --> 00:39:41,630
The leather cracked
after less than a week.

1105
00:39:42,710 --> 00:39:44,760
Let me ask you, was that you?

1106
00:39:45,840 --> 00:39:47,300
Aren't you from Mianyang?

1107
00:39:47,320 --> 00:39:49,180
Since when are you from Tiecheng?

1108
00:39:50,510 --> 00:39:51,630
On my grandmother's side,

1109
00:39:51,630 --> 00:39:53,230
I really am from Mianyang.

1110
00:39:53,320 --> 00:39:55,050
Who cares which side you claim!

1111
00:39:56,080 --> 00:39:57,140
What are you doing?

1112
00:39:57,190 --> 00:39:58,480
-Hey, don't get physical!
-What do you think you're doing?

1113
00:39:58,480 --> 00:39:59,670
Why don't you take out your ID card

1114
00:39:59,670 --> 00:40:00,920
and show it to everyone?
That'll settle it.

1115
00:40:00,920 --> 00:40:01,920
I've noticed something—

1116
00:40:01,920 --> 00:40:04,230
he's been picking on us country folks
from the start.

1117
00:40:04,230 --> 00:40:05,920
Director Zheng, see? I told you.

1118
00:40:05,920 --> 00:40:07,460
It's not easy for us
to get together like this!

1119
00:40:07,460 --> 00:40:09,530
I don't know what it is about Tiecheng

1120
00:40:09,920 --> 00:40:11,440
that produces someone like him!

1121
00:40:11,440 --> 00:40:12,110
Don't get angry.

1122
00:40:12,110 --> 00:40:13,020
It's no fun anymore.

1123
00:40:13,020 --> 00:40:13,480
Well...

1124
00:40:14,920 --> 00:40:16,520
With that glib tongue of his,

1125
00:40:16,590 --> 00:40:19,120
he doesn't seem like
he's from Tiecheng to me.

1126
00:40:22,800 --> 00:40:23,670
Xiaoyi!

1127
00:40:24,710 --> 00:40:25,400
Weijie?

1128
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:27,590
-Come join us.
-It's been so long.

1129
00:40:27,590 --> 00:40:28,440
Long time no see.

1130
00:40:28,440 --> 00:40:30,110
That belt last time was really nice.

1131
00:40:30,110 --> 00:40:30,590
Not bad, right?

1132
00:40:30,590 --> 00:40:32,800
-Yeah.
-I just got a new batch of phone pouches.

1133
00:40:32,800 --> 00:40:33,830
Do you want to take a look?

1134
00:40:33,830 --> 00:40:34,440
Let me see.

1135
00:40:34,440 --> 00:40:34,840
Look.

1136
00:40:35,320 --> 00:40:36,920
I really didn't expect this.

1137
00:40:37,110 --> 00:40:39,320
A small Tiecheng
hometown association gathering,

1138
00:40:39,320 --> 00:40:41,110
and we ended up with two impostors.

1139
00:40:41,110 --> 00:40:42,510
That's enough. Sit down.

1140
00:40:42,670 --> 00:40:43,670
Stop talking.

1141
00:40:44,670 --> 00:40:45,130
Well...

1142
00:40:45,670 --> 00:40:47,110
Why is the mood so down?

1143
00:40:47,110 --> 00:40:49,040
Come on. Let's have another drink.

1144
00:40:49,230 --> 00:40:49,960
He left, so let him go.

1145
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:51,320
But we should stay happy,

1146
00:40:51,320 --> 00:40:52,110
-right?
-Right.

1147
00:40:52,110 --> 00:40:53,480
It's not easy for us to get together!

1148
00:40:53,480 --> 00:40:53,960
Come on.

1149
00:40:54,150 --> 00:40:54,670
Cheers.

1150
00:40:54,670 --> 00:40:55,480
Director Zheng,

1151
00:40:55,480 --> 00:40:57,580
I just remembered I've got something to do
this afternoon.

1152
00:40:57,580 --> 00:40:58,510
So I'll be going.

1153
00:40:58,800 --> 00:41:00,660
You've barely touched your food.

1154
00:41:01,240 --> 00:41:02,330
Stay a little longer.

1155
00:41:02,330 --> 00:41:03,440
Yeah, what could be more important

1156
00:41:03,440 --> 00:41:05,110
than a hometown gathering?

1157
00:41:06,030 --> 00:41:07,070
There's

1158
00:41:07,480 --> 00:41:09,800
no one else here
from the East Chemical Plant!

1159
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:11,070
You guys,

1160
00:41:11,150 --> 00:41:13,280
why are you all so petty?

1161
00:41:15,530 --> 00:41:16,410
I really have something to do.

1162
00:41:16,410 --> 00:41:18,210
Director Zheng, how about this?

1163
00:41:18,320 --> 00:41:19,660
Since we're having a meal here,

1164
00:41:19,660 --> 00:41:21,260
shouldn't we split the bill?

1165
00:41:21,510 --> 00:41:21,920
Take this.

1166
00:41:21,920 --> 00:41:23,050
Put your money away.

1167
00:41:23,630 --> 00:41:25,090
Alright, I won't keep you.

1168
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:26,400
But today's meal

1169
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:27,070
is on me.

1170
00:41:27,230 --> 00:41:29,750
I'm treating
all my little brothers and sisters.

1171
00:41:29,750 --> 00:41:31,230
Let's keep in touch from now on.

1172
00:41:31,230 --> 00:41:33,290
Just let me know if you need anything.

1173
00:41:33,440 --> 00:41:34,070
Put it away.

1174
00:41:34,070 --> 00:41:35,670
Okay. I'm sorry, Director Zheng.

1175
00:41:35,670 --> 00:41:36,190
It's fine.

1176
00:41:36,190 --> 00:41:37,110
I really have something to do.
I'll get going.

1177
00:41:37,110 --> 00:41:37,830
Okay, okay.

1178
00:41:42,320 --> 00:41:43,630
Come on, everyone.

1179
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:44,230
Come on.

1180
00:41:44,320 --> 00:41:45,440
Let them leave.

1181
00:41:45,590 --> 00:41:46,880
Let's keep drinking.

1182
00:41:47,030 --> 00:41:47,550
Come on!

1183
00:41:49,840 --> 00:41:50,360
Hey!

1184
00:41:52,270 --> 00:41:53,590
Bro, call me if you need anything.

1185
00:41:53,590 --> 00:41:54,110
Okay.

1186
00:41:56,990 --> 00:41:58,120
Wait. Wait a second.

1187
00:41:58,400 --> 00:41:59,200
What's wrong?

1188
00:42:01,590 --> 00:42:02,720
Come sit for a while.

1189
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:04,060
Sit with me.

1190
00:42:04,320 --> 00:42:04,840
Come on.

1191
00:42:05,480 --> 00:42:06,150
What for?

1192
00:42:07,030 --> 00:42:07,440
Sit.

1193
00:42:07,840 --> 00:42:09,370
Sit for a while. Let's chat.

1194
00:42:12,590 --> 00:42:13,920
Why did you come out too?

1195
00:42:15,230 --> 00:42:16,360
Feels suffocating.

1196
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:18,300
Suffocating in there, wasn't it?

1197
00:42:18,670 --> 00:42:20,000
Just admit it—

1198
00:42:20,230 --> 00:42:21,960
Tiecheng doesn't welcome you.

1199
00:42:22,320 --> 00:42:24,990
How about we go to the Fujian
hometown association gathering?

1200
00:42:24,990 --> 00:42:26,920
Wait. Where are you actually from?

1201
00:42:27,280 --> 00:42:29,230
When I'm with Tiecheng folks,
I'm from Tiecheng.

1202
00:42:29,230 --> 00:42:31,690
When I'm with Fujian folks,
I'm from Fujian.

1203
00:42:33,190 --> 00:42:34,280
So you came to the gatherings

1204
00:42:34,280 --> 00:42:35,810
really just to sell things?

1205
00:42:37,030 --> 00:42:37,760
What else?

1206
00:42:38,670 --> 00:42:39,930
I'm studying finance.

1207
00:42:40,110 --> 00:42:41,480
I run a small business

1208
00:42:41,880 --> 00:42:43,410
and try to get some clients.

1209
00:42:43,480 --> 00:42:44,670
Many of them are my clients.

1210
00:42:44,670 --> 00:42:46,810
Aren't you embarrassed if you get caught?

1211
00:42:46,810 --> 00:42:48,750
What's there to be embarrassed about?

1212
00:42:48,750 --> 00:42:50,230
As the saying goes,

1213
00:42:50,590 --> 00:42:52,320
the thick-skinned get their fill,

1214
00:42:52,320 --> 00:42:54,150
while the thin-skinned starve.

1215
00:42:55,260 --> 00:42:57,180
You didn't get any just now, did you?

1216
00:42:57,180 --> 00:42:58,590
I'll take you to Cafeteria No. 2.

1217
00:42:58,590 --> 00:42:59,230
My treat.

1218
00:42:59,480 --> 00:43:00,320
I... I'll pass.

1219
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:01,320
I really have things to do.

1220
00:43:01,320 --> 00:43:02,320
I still have some things to handle.
